CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 15, 1962, pg. 17 reads: "Beautiful Yard Awards Program - Cultivators of above-average yards in Homewood attended the seventh annual awards program and tea sponsored by the Homewood Community Improvement Association...In the photo at the upper right, yard inspection committee members relax after the difficult task of selecting the award-winning yards. Left to right, seated: Mrs. Audrey Jones, Louie Chatman, Mrs. Rose Jones and Mrs. Jennie Thompson.  Standing: James Doyle, McKinley Tomlin, Charles Bennett, Albert Brown, Lawrence Bush, John Jones, Arthur Purdie, Elmer Cobb and David Buckner...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of yard inspection committee members, from left, seated: Audrey Jones, Louie Chatman, Rose Jones, and Jennie Thompson; standing: James Doyle, McKinley Tomlin, Charles Bennett, Albert Brown, Lawrence Bush, John Jones, Arthur Purdie, Elmer Cobb, and David Buckner, gathered behind folding table in Bethesda United Presbyterian Church during seventh annual beautiful yard awards program
